eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli reports. DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal flood victims are raising the alarm about the inhumane conditions they are facing at temporary housing units. Victims who were moved from community halls last year say they are now living in overcrowded flats, with some sharing a room with over 12 people. Human Settlements Minister, Mmamoloko Kubayi visited some of the affected residents that are pleading for urgent intervention. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli reports.